{
  "text": "Although for most cases the classical hydrostatic equation suffices, when the gravitational field becomes strong, using a general relativistic version of the hydrostatic equilibrium equation becomes inevitable. If one starts from a spherically symmetric metric assuming an isotropic energymomentum tensor one ends with the famous TOV equation [CITATION_1] ",
